<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Mobile Marketing | Nice & Next StyleUp</title>

<style>

*{
    margin:0;
    padding:0;
    box-sizing:border-box;
    font-family:'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
}

body{
    background: linear-gradient(120deg,#fdfbfb,#ebedee);
}

/* HEADER */
header{
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #2c3e50, #34495e);
    padding:15px 40px;
    display:flex;
    justify-content:space-between;
    align-items:center;
    color:white;
}

header h1{ font-size:26px; }

nav a{
    color:white;
    text-decoration:none;
    margin:0 18px;
    font-size:17px;
}
nav a:hover{ color:#f1c40f; }

/* HERO */
.hero{
    padding:80px 20px;
    text-align:center;
    background:#2c3e50;
    color:white;
}

.hero h2{
    font-size:42px;
    margin-bottom:20px;
}

.hero p{
    font-size:20px;
    max-width:800px;
    margin:auto;
}

/* BLOG SECTION */
.section{
    padding:70px 50px;
    text-align:center;
}

.blog-container{
    display:flex;
    flex-wrap:wrap;
    gap:30px;
    justify-content:center;
    margin-top:40px;
}

.blog-card{
    background:white;
    width:320px;
    padding:25px;
    border-radius:15px;
    box-shadow:0 10px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    text-align:left;
    transition:0.3s;
}

.blog-card:hover{
    transform:translateY(-8px);
}

.blog-card h3{
    margin-bottom:15px;
    color:#2c3e50;
}

.blog-card p{
    color:#555;
    font-size:15px;
}

footer{
    background:#2c3e50;
    color:white;
    padding:20px;
    text-align:center;
}

</style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
    <h1>Nice & Next StyleUp</h1>
    <nav>
        <a href="smmproject.html">Home</a>
        <a href="shop.html">Shop</a>
        <a href="mobile-marketing.html">Mobile Marketing</a>
        <a href="blog.html">Blog</a>
    </nav>
</header>

<!-- INTRO SECTION -->
<section class="hero">
    <h2>Mobile Marketing</h2>
    <p>
        Mobile marketing is a digital marketing strategy focused on reaching users 
        through smartphones and tablets. It includes mobile apps, SMS marketing, 
        social media advertising, search ads, and location-based targeting. 
        With most internet users accessing content through mobile devices, 
        mobile marketing helps businesses connect directly with customers anytime, anywhere.
    </p>
</section>

<!-- BLOG SECTION -->
<section class="section">
    <h2>Mobile Marketing Blog Topics</h2>

    <div class="blog-container">

        <!-- 1 -->
        <div class="blog-card">
            <h3>1. App-Based Marketing</h3>
            <p>
                This is mobile advertising involving mobile apps. While 80% of mobile time is spent engaged with apps,
                you don’t have to create an app yourself. Services like Google AdMob help advertisers create mobile ads
                that appear within third-party apps. Facebook also integrates mobile promoted posts seamlessly into
                users' news feeds.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 2 -->
        <div class="blog-card">
            <h3>2. In-Game Mobile Marketing</h3>
            <p>
                In-game mobile marketing refers to ads that appear inside mobile games.
                These ads can be banner popups, full-page images, or video ads shown between
                loading screens. It allows brands to target engaged users during gameplay.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 3 -->
        <div class="blog-card">
            <h3>3. QR Codes</h3>
            <p>
                QR codes are scanned by users to access a specific webpage.
                They are often linked with mobile gamification and promotional campaigns.
                Users scan the code without always knowing what surprise or offer awaits them.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 4 -->
        <div class="blog-card">
            <h3>4. Location-Based Marketing</h3>
            <p>
                Location-based ads appear based on a user’s geographic location.
                Businesses can target customers within a specific radius, such as
                1 mile from their store, increasing the chances of real-time engagement.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 5 -->
        <div class="blog-card">
            <h3>5. Mobile Search Ads</h3>
            <p>
                Mobile search ads are Google search ads designed specifically for mobile devices.
                They often include extensions like click-to-call buttons, directions,
                and map integrations to improve user convenience.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 6 -->
        <div class="blog-card">
            <h3>6. Mobile Apps</h3>
            <p>
                A mobile app is a software application developed for smartphones and tablets.
                These apps are designed to meet device constraints and use features like
                GPS, camera, and accelerometer. Gaming apps often use motion sensors
                to enhance user experience.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<footer>
    © 2026 Nice & Next StyleUp | Mobile Marketing Page
</footer>

</body>
</html>
